      <tr><td> <h2 name="overview"><strong><a name="bestdebate" id="bestdebate"></a>Best Debates Structure </strong></h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p>Best Debates is a structure that invites you to
                create<strong> Interactives</strong>. Interactives are arguments,
                evidence or logic in discreet entries so that the power of each
                Interactive stands on its own and isn't diluted by additional material.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>At first, it may seem awkward to create <strong>one
                  entry per thought or fact</strong>; but as you do this you will see that
                the power of clarity leverages your best ideas, facts and logic.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p> In fact, some users discover that clarity trumps
                logic and persuasion. Even the best ideas, logic and facts become lost
                when combined with other entries, reducing their power to the weakest
                link in the chain.</p>
            </li>
          </ul></td></tr>
